23	// US-047 — Creator "My Submissions" tab. Mirrors the US-043 applications
24	// screen: calls `list_my_submissions` (SECURITY DEFINER, scoped to the
25	// caller's applications) and renders three segments matching the
26	// submission_status enum (pending / approved / rejected). Press routes
27	// to the listing detail so creators can re-read the brief; submissions
28	// have no dedicated detail screen in v1.
29	//
30	// Realtime: subscribes to UPDATE events on public.submissions. The
31	// submissions table has no direct creator_id column, so we omit the
32	// server-side filter and let the broker's RLS evaluation
33	// (`submissions_creator_rw`, join-through-applications) gate visibility.
34	// Same `supabase.realtime.setAuth(token)` flow as US-044. Publication
35	// update lands in the companion migration
36	// `us_047_submissions_realtime_publication`. Under the DevRolePicker
37	// session the literal dev token is rejected by the broker (Codebase
38	// Pattern #122) — empty-state screenshots verify wiring only.
39	//
40	// Spec gap: AC text calls the file `submitted.tsx`, but the TabBar
41	// route established in US-031 is `/(creator)/submissions`. Renaming the
42	// file would invalidate the established routing convention, so the file
43	// name stays as `submissions.tsx` while the header renders "Submitted"
44	// per docs/design.md §3.1 tab label.
